In [ ]:
desc = df.describe(include="all").drop(columns="emp_no")
iqr_salario = scipy.stats.iqr(df.salario)
desc.loc["IQR"] = desc.loc["75%"] - desc.loc["25%"]
desc.loc["min_outlier"] = desc.loc["25%"] - 1.5*desc.loc["IQR"]
desc.loc["max_outlier"] = desc.loc["75%"] + 1.5*desc.loc["IQR"]

#DROP OUTLIERS
df_drop = df.copy()
for col in df_drop.columns:

    if col in desc.columns and not np.isnan(desc.loc["IQR", col]):
        df_drop = df_drop[(df_drop[col] >= desc.loc["min_outlier", col]) & (df_drop[col] <= desc.loc["max_outlier", col])]

#IMPUTE MEAN OUTLIERS
df_mean = df.copy()
for col in df_mean.columns:

    if col in desc.columns and not np.isnan(desc.loc["IQR", col]):
        min_col, max_col = desc.loc[["min_outlier", "max_outlier"], col]
        df_mean.loc[df_mean[col] <= min_col, col] = df_mean[col].mean()
        df_mean.loc[df_mean[col] >= max_col, col] = df_mean[col].mean()

#IMPUTE WINSORIZE OUTLIERS
df_win = df.copy()
for col in df_win.columns:

    if col in desc.columns and not np.isnan(desc.loc["IQR", col]):
        min_col, max_col = desc.loc[["min_outlier", "max_outlier"], col]
        df_win.loc[df_win[col] <= min_col, col] = min_col
        df_win.loc[df_win[col] >= max_col, col] = max_col

freq = df.departamento.value_counts().to_frame().reset_index()
freq.columns = ["Departamento", "fi"]
In [ ]:
freq["Fi"] = freq["fi"].cumsum()
freq["hi"] = freq["fi"]/freq.fi.sum()
freq["Hi"] = freq.hi.cumsum()
